<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="208" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="0.[136,1452,1689,1817]" pageId="0" pageNumber="208">
Most similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="N. Tanaka" authorityYear="2010" baseAuthorityName="Wang &amp; Tang" baseAuthorityYear="1949" box="[289,425,1689,1711]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Rohdea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="0" pageNumber="208" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pachynema">
<emphasis box="[289,425,1689,1711]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="208">R. pachynema</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in sharing a long slender subterranean stolon, but differs mainly by the longer inner bracts, larger flowers, and columnar filaments adnate to middle or base of perianth lobes and not connate to adjacent ones.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
