<subSubSection lastPageId="1" lastPageNumber="209" pageId="0" pageNumber="208" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="0.[136,1452,1861,2064]" lastBlockId="1.[136,1452,158,783]" lastPageId="1" lastPageNumber="209" pageId="0" pageNumber="208">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,274,1861,1887]" pageId="0" pageNumber="208">Description</emphasis>
:—Plant herbaceous, perennial, rhizomatous. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[791,892,1861,1888]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="208">Rhizome</emphasis>
fleshy, cylindrical, (3)5–10(13) cm long, (1.5)3– 3(3.5) cm in diameter, externally greenish grey, internally white or cream, with many annular leaf scars, internodes (0.3)0.5–2(2.5) cm long, producing long slender subterranean stolons to 
<quantity box="[930,997,1932,1959]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.5" pageId="0" pageNumber="208" unit="cm" value="65.0">65 cm</quantity>
or longer, 
<quantity box="[1113,1246,1932,1959]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" metricValueMax="4.5" metricValueMin="2.5" pageId="0" pageNumber="208" unit="mm" value="3.5" valueMax="4.5" valueMin="2.5">2.5–4.5 mm</quantity>
in diameter. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1386,1451,1932,1958]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="208">Roots</emphasis>
cordlike, (2)2.5–3(4) mm in diameter, fleshy, velutinous. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[778,836,1967,1993]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="208">Stem</emphasis>
ascending, nearly erect, cylindrical, (2)4.5–8(10.5) cm long, (1)2.5–3(4) cm in diameter, brown or light orange, bearing 8–13 leaves. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[998,1077,2003,2029]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="208">Leaves</emphasis>
basal, equitant, narrowly oblongelliptic, somewhat undulate, recurved, coriaceous, up to 
<quantity box="[764,833,2038,2064]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="0" pageNumber="208" unit="cm" value="60.0">60 cm</quantity>
long and 
<quantity box="[942,997,2037,2064]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="0" pageNumber="208" unit="cm" value="5.0">5 cm</quantity>
wide, dark green and somewhat lustrous adaxially, green and paler abaxially, smoot on both sides, margin entire; midrib adaxially impressed and abaxially raised; secondary veins numerous, parallel, closely spaced at intervals of (1.0)1.5–2.0(2.5) mm. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1215,1322,193,220]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="209">Peduncle</emphasis>
semiterete, 
<quantity box="[136,262,228,255]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" metricValueMax="9.5" metricValueMin="6.5" pageId="1" pageNumber="209" unit="cm" value="8.0" valueMax="9.5" valueMin="6.5">6.5–9.5 cm</quantity>
long, (0.4)0.5–0.6(0.7) cm in diameter, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[716,873,228,255]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="209">Inflorescence</emphasis>
a spike of ca. 7–12 flowers, cylindrical, ca. 
<quantity box="[1374,1451,228,255]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.5" pageId="1" pageNumber="209" unit="cm" value="6.5">6.5 cm</quantity>
long, ca. 5.0 cm in diameter; rachis fleshy. Flower-subtending bracts and bracteoles white with green tint to pale green or yellowish green, subcoriaceous; margin entire, membranous, whitish. Flower-subtending bract lanceolate, (1.8)2–2.5(3.0) cm long, (2)2.4–3.5(4) mm wide at base; margin entire; distal bracts longer than proximal ones, mostly longer than flowers. Bracteole linear, 8–9.5(11) mm long, (0.5)1–1.5(2) mm wide at base. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1167,1260,369,396]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="209">Flowers</emphasis>
sessile, borne in shallow pits between ridges on rachis, facing almost horizontally except for some distal flowers facing slightly upward. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,240,440,466]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="209">Perigone</emphasis>
(nearly) funnel-shaped, with tube and 6 lobes, (2.0)2.3–2.5(2.8) cm in diameter, fleshy, green, turning yellow at late anthesis; perigone tube broadly crateriform, (8.8)9.0–10.0(12.0) mm long, (21.0)22.0–24.5(25.0) mm in diameter; perianth segments often obliquely ascending, broadly ovate, (4.5)5–5.5(5.8) mm long, (4.3)4.8–5.2(5.5) mm wide at base, margin entire, apex subacute to obtuse and deflexed. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[949,1047,545,571]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="209">Stamens</emphasis>
6, inserted at bases or middle parts of perigone lobes; filaments columniform, ca. 
<quantity box="[668,756,580,607]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="1" pageNumber="209" unit="mm" value="2.5">2.5 mm</quantity>
long, not dilated toward base; anthers dorsifixed, biloculate, introrse, orbicular-ovate, retuse proximally and distally, 0.8–0.9(1) mm long, 
<quantity box="[1043,1161,616,643]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.25" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="209" unit="mm" value="1.25" valueMax="1.5" valueMin="1.0">1–1.5 mm</quantity>
wide, facing downward. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,195,650,677]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="209">Pistil</emphasis>
1, tricarpellate, erect, 4.5–5.2(5.5) mm long; ovary superior, ovoid, (2.4)3.0– 
<quantity box="[1072,1160,651,678]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.2" pageId="1" pageNumber="209" unit="mm" value="3.2">3.2 mm</quantity>
long, 2.3–2.6(3.1) mm in diameter (broadest below middle), 3-locular, with scattered white minute dots; style conspicuous, 2.3–2.5(2.7) mm long, 0.7–0.8(1.3) mm in diameter; stigma positioned nearly at the same level with anthers, trisected, 
<quantity box="[1255,1389,722,748]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="209" unit="mm" value="0.3" valueMax="0.4" valueMin="0.2">0.2–0.4 mm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity box="[136,271,756,783]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" metricValueMax="8.0" metricValueMin="6.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="209" unit="mm" value="0.7" valueMax="0.8" valueMin="0.6">0.6–0.8 mm</quantity>
wide, erect, surface papillulate. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[634,706,756,782]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="209">Fruits</emphasis>
not seen.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
