<subSubSection lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="211" pageId="2" pageNumber="210" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[136,1452,1580,2075]" lastBlockId="3.[136,1452,158,436]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="211" pageId="2" pageNumber="210">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,481,1652,1678]" pageId="2" pageNumber="210">Taxonomic relationships</emphasis>
:—In 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Roth" authorityYear="1821" box="[547,633,1652,1678]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Rohdea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="2" pageNumber="210" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[547,633,1652,1678]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="210">Rohdea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
only two species, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="H. Z. Feng &amp; Q. X. Han" authorityYear="2022" box="[838,998,1652,1678]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Rohdea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="2" pageNumber="210" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="grandiflora">
<emphasis box="[838,998,1652,1678]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="210">R. grandiflora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Wang &amp; Tang 1949: 18) N. Tanaka (2010: 35)" authorityName="N. Tanaka" authorityPageNumber="35" authorityYear="2010" baseAuthorityName="Wang &amp; Tang" baseAuthorityPageNumber="18" baseAuthorityYear="1949" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Rohdea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="2" pageNumber="210" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pachynema">
<emphasis box="[1052,1211,1652,1678]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="210">R. pachynema</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Wang, F. T. &amp; Tang, T." pageId="2" pageNumber="210" pagination="105 - 114" refId="ref2451" refString="Wang, F. T. &amp; Tang, T. (1949) Notes on Chinese Liliaceae VIII. Contributions from the Institute of Botany 6: 105 - 114." type="journal article" year="1949">Wang &amp; Tang 1949: 18</bibRefCitation>
) N. 
<bibRefCitation author="Tanaka, N." box="[205,416,1688,1715]" pageId="2" pageNumber="210" pagination="1 - 54" refId="ref2388" refString="Tanaka, N. (2010) A taxonomic revision of the genus Rohdea (Asparagaceae). Makinoa New Series 9: 1 - 54." type="book chapter" year="2010">Tanaka (2010: 35)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[434,624,1688,1715]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[136,229,1476,1498]" captionTargetBox="[215,1372,190,1452]" captionTargetId="figure-18@2.[215,1372,190,1452]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. A. Inflorescence of Rohdea grandiflora. B. Inflorescence of R. pachynema (some perianth lobes removed). C &amp; D. Flower of R. pachynema" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777006" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777006/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="210">Fig. 2 B, C &amp; D</figureCitation>
), have a long slender stolon, suggesting that the two species are close in relationship. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="H. Z. Feng &amp; Q. X. Han" authorityYear="2022" box="[286,511,1724,1750]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Rohdea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="2" pageNumber="210" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="grandiflora">
<emphasis box="[286,511,1724,1750]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="210">Rohdea grandiflora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is easily distinguishable from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="N. Tanaka" authorityYear="2010" baseAuthorityName="Wang &amp; Tang" baseAuthorityYear="1949" box="[874,1037,1724,1750]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Rohdea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="2" pageNumber="210" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pachynema">
<emphasis box="[874,1037,1724,1750]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="210">R. pachynema</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
mainly by the longer bracts, larger flowers (23–25 vs. 
<quantity box="[357,466,1760,1787]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.5" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="7.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="210" unit="mm" value="8.5" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="7.0">7–10 mm</quantity>
across), filaments inserted in the middle or basal portion (vs. subdistal portion) of the perianth lobe, not broadly dilated (vs. dilated) toward base, and not connate (vs. connate) to adjacent ones. 
<bibRefCitation author="Tanaka, N." pageId="2" pageNumber="210" pagination="1 - 54" refId="ref2388" refString="Tanaka, N. (2010) A taxonomic revision of the genus Rohdea (Asparagaceae). Makinoa New Series 9: 1 - 54." type="book chapter" year="2010">Tanaka (2010)</bibRefCitation>
presumed that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="N. Tanaka" authorityYear="2010" baseAuthorityName="Wang &amp; Tang" baseAuthorityYear="1949" box="[381,539,1832,1858]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Rohdea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="2" pageNumber="210" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pachynema">
<emphasis box="[381,539,1832,1858]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="210">R. pachynema</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a descendant from the ancestral lineage of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Tanaka 2019)" baseAuthorityName="Tanaka" baseAuthorityYear="2019" box="[1044,1330,1832,1858]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Rohdea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="2" pageNumber="210" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fargesii">
<emphasis box="[1044,1160,1832,1858]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="210">R. fargesii</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Tanaka, N." box="[1173,1322,1832,1858]" pageId="2" pageNumber="210" pagination="48 - 50" refId="ref2415" refString="Tanaka, N. (2019) Rohdea henryi, the replacement name for R. chinensis, and a new combination for its variety (Asparagaceae). Phytotaxa 400: 48 - 50." type="journal article" year="2019">Tanaka 2019</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, in that the filaments of these two species inserted at base of perianth lobe, incurved, decurrent parts on tube usually dilated and united with adjacent ones, forming small protuberance at each junction. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="H. Z. Feng &amp; Q. X. Han" authorityYear="2022" box="[939,1098,1904,1930]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Rohdea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="2" pageNumber="210" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="grandiflora">
<emphasis box="[939,1098,1904,1930]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="210">R. grandiflora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, appears to be the sister species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="N. Tanaka" authorityYear="2010" baseAuthorityName="Wang &amp; Tang" baseAuthorityYear="1949" box="[169,331,1940,1966]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Rohdea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="2" pageNumber="210" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pachynema">
<emphasis box="[169,331,1940,1966]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="210">R. pachynema</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, was also descended from the ancestral lineage of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Tanaka" baseAuthorityYear="2019" box="[926,1045,1940,1966]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Rohdea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="2" pageNumber="210" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fargesii">
<emphasis box="[926,1045,1940,1966]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="210">R. fargesii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but the filaments adnate to middle or base of perianth lobes and not connate to adjacent ones. Based on Raunkiaer (1934) the species have stolon that belongs to Cryptophytes which adapted well to the alpine climate characterized by low temperature and short growing season. The distribution area of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="N. Tanaka" authorityYear="2010" baseAuthorityName="Wang &amp; Tang" baseAuthorityYear="1949" box="[489,647,2048,2074]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Rohdea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="2" pageNumber="210" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pachynema">
<emphasis box="[489,647,2048,2074]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="210">R. pachynema</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a high altitude (e.g. 
<quantity box="[914,998,2048,2075]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.7" pageId="2" pageNumber="210" unit="m" value="3700.0">3700 m</quantity>
in 
<emphasis box="[1031,1208,2048,2075]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="210">G.H. Yang 3896</emphasis>
, PE00593144) and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="H. Z. Feng &amp; Q. X. Han" authorityYear="2022" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Rohdea" kingdom="Plantae" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="211" order="Asparagales" pageId="2" pageNumber="210" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="grandiflora">
<emphasis italics="true" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="211" pageId="2" pageNumber="210">R. grandiflora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also distributed at the highest latitude, where a colder climate prevails than in the central or southern part of the generic range. Development of long slender stolon in the two species may also reflect the colder climate which beneficial to reproduction after abortion in cold environment in spring.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
